By Joy Kaka Abuja – A Kubwa Grade 1 Area Court on Thursday remanded a 40-year-old man, Oshodi Onyminyi, in prison for allegedly causing grievous hurt.The Judge, Ibrahim Balarabe, remanded the defendant in prison and adjourned the matter until July 3, for his bail to be considered.The defendant, who is of Arab Road, Kubwa, Abuja, was charged with causing grievous hurt.The Prosecutor, John Okpa, told the court that one Bala Iliya of Maitama Kubwa, Abuja, reported the matter at the Kubwa Police Station on May 8.He said the defendant acted violently without provocation and pushed the complainant in a pit at the complainant’s farm in Arab Road, Kubwa, Abuja.“The complainant sustained an injury in his rib and was rushed to Kubwa General Hospital and later transferred to an Orthopaedic Hospital in Garki 2, Abuja, where he was admitted,” he said.Okpa said the offence contravened Section 247 of the Penal Code.The defendant pleaded not guilty.